    19Ôćĺ
    20Ôćĺ**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21ÔćĺIt is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22Ôćĺeasily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23Ôćĺ
    24Ôćĺ* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25Ôćĺ* Integrated [search] support
    26Ôćĺ* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27Ôćĺ* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28Ôćĺ* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29Ôćĺ* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    46Ôćĺ## Contributing
    48ÔćĺmdBook is free and open source. You can find the source code on
    49Ôćĺ[GitHub](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook) and issues and feature requests can be posted on
    50Ôćĺthe [GitHub issue tracker](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues). mdBook relies on the community to fix bugs and
    51Ôćĺadd features: if you'd like to contribute, please read
    52Ôćĺthe [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guide and consider opening
    53Ôćĺa [pull request](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pulls).
    54Ôćĺ
    55Ôćĺ## License
    57ÔćĺThe mdBook source and documentation are released under
    58Ôćĺthe [Mozilla Public License v2.0](https://www.mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/).
