for_developers/README.md
     1Ôćĺ# For developers
     3ÔćĺWhile `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4Ôćĺunderlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5Ôćĺflexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6Ôćĺconsumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7Ôćĺthe book or render it in a different format.
     8Ôćĺ
     9ÔćĺThe *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10Ôćĺ`mdbook`.
    11Ôćĺ
    12ÔćĺThe two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15Ôćĺ- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16Ôćĺ
    17Ôćĺ## The build process
    19ÔćĺThe process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20Ôćĺ
    21Ôćĺ1. Load the book
    22Ôćĺ    - Parse the `book.toml`, falling back to the default `Config` if it doesn't
    23Ôćĺ       exist
    24Ôćĺ    - Load the book chapters into memory
    25Ôćĺ    - Discover which preprocessors/backends should be used
    26Ôćĺ2. For each backend:
    27Ôćĺ   1. Run all the preprocessors.
    28Ôćĺ   2. Call the backend to render the processed result.
    29Ôćĺ
    30Ôćĺ## Using `mdbook` as a library
    32ÔćĺThe `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33Ôćĺexposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34Ôćĺprogrammatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
    35ÔćĺThis can be used to add your own functionality or tweak the build process.
    36Ôćĺ
    37ÔćĺThe easiest way to find out how to use the `mdbook-driver` crate is by looking at the
    38Ôćĺ[API Docs]. The top level documentation explains how one would use the
    39Ôćĺ[`MDBook`] type to load and build a book, while the [config] module gives a good
    40Ôćĺexplanation on the configuration system.
    41Ôćĺ
    42Ôćĺ[`MDBook`]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/struct.MDBook.html
    43Ôćĺ[API Docs]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/
    44Ôćĺ[config]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/config/index.html
