format/mdbook.md
     1Ôćĺ# mdBook-specific features ÔÇŽ
     3Ôćĺ## Hiding code lines
     5ÔćĺThere is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6Ôćĺ
     7ÔćĺFor the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8ÔćĺThis prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9Ôćĺ
    10Ôćĺ[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11Ôćĺ
    12Ôćĺ```bash
    13Ôćĺ# fn main() {
    14Ôćĺ    let x = 5;
    15Ôćĺ    let y = 6;
    16Ôćĺ
    17Ôćĺ    println!("{}", x + y);
    18Ôćĺ# }
    19Ôćĺ```
    20Ôćĺ
    21ÔćĺWill render as
    22Ôćĺ
    23Ôćĺ```rust
    24Ôćĺ# fn main() {
    25Ôćĺ    let x = 5;
    26Ôćĺ    let y = 6;
    27Ôćĺ
    28Ôćĺ    println!("{}", x + y);
    29Ôćĺ# }
    30Ôćĺ```
    31Ôćĺ
    32ÔćĺWhen you tap or hover the mouse over the code block, there will be an eyeball icon (<i class="fa fa-eye"></i>) which will toggle the visibility of the hidden lines.
    33Ôćĺ
    34ÔćĺBy default, this only works for code examples that are annotated with `rust`.
    35ÔćĺHowever, you can define custom prefixes for other languages by adding a new line-hiding prefix in your `book.toml` with the language name and prefix character(s):
    36Ôćĺ
    37Ôćĺ```toml
    38Ôćĺ[output.html.code.hidelines]
    39Ôćĺpython = "~"
    40Ôćĺ```
    41Ôćĺ
    42ÔćĺThe prefix will hide any lines that begin with the given prefix. With the python prefix shown above, this:
    43Ôćĺ
    44Ôćĺ```bash
    45Ôćĺ~hidden()
    46Ôćĺnothidden():
    47Ôćĺ~    hidden()
    48Ôćĺ    ~hidden()
    49Ôćĺ    nothidden()
    50Ôćĺ```
    51Ôćĺ
    52Ôćĺwill render as
    53Ôćĺ
    54Ôćĺ```python
    55Ôćĺ~hidden()
    56Ôćĺnothidden():
    57Ôćĺ~    hidden()
    58Ôćĺ    ~hidden()
    59Ôćĺ    nothidden()
    60Ôćĺ```
    61Ôćĺ
    62ÔćĺThis behavior can be overridden locally with a different prefix. This has the same effect as above:
    63Ôćĺ
    64Ôćĺ~~~markdown
    65Ôćĺ```python,hidelines=!!!
    66Ôćĺ!!!hidden()
    67Ôćĺnothidden():
    68Ôćĺ!!!    hidden()
    69Ôćĺ    !!!hidden()
    70Ôćĺ    nothidden()
    71Ôćĺ```
    72Ôćĺ~~~
    73Ôćĺ
