format/theme/README.md
     1Ôćĺ# Theme
     3ÔćĺThe default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4Ôćĺrender your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5Ôćĺbinary.
     6Ôćĺ
     7ÔćĺThe theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8Ôćĺthe theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9Ôćĺproject root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10Ôćĺand now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11Ôćĺ
    12ÔćĺHere are the files you can override:
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
    15Ôćĺ- **_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section.
    16Ôćĺ- **_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page.
    17Ôćĺ- **_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book.
    18Ôćĺ    - **_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements.
    19Ôćĺ    - **_css/general.css_** is the base styles.
    20Ôćĺ    - **_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output.
    21Ôćĺ    - **_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files.
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
